# Event Listeners

- addEventListener takes TWO arguments
- The first argument is the type of even that we are listening for
- You can have any number of things happen because it is a function

```jsx
button.addEventListener('click', function(){
  console.log('Yoo this is crazy')
  button.style.color = 'pink'
  button.style.backgroundColor = 'blue'
  for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    console.log(i)
  }
})
```

- eventListeners use anonymous functions inside
- eventHandlers can use functions outside of the function
- everything in javascript is an object (it has properties and methods)
